WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.460 --> 00:00:04.420
No matter what I do to you.
you should just take it.

2
00:00:04.550 --> 00:00:06.660
The fact that I'm a murderer's son

3
00:00:06.930 --> 00:00:09.740
is not a reason for you to belittle me.

4
00:00:10.600 --> 00:00:11.530
Is that so?

5
00:00:12.200 --> 00:00:14.530
Then why are you still here?

6
00:00:14.770 --> 00:00:18.240
You should know I hate people like you.

7
00:00:18.360 --> 00:00:20.160
Because I don't want to run away.

8
00:00:20.250 --> 00:00:23.680
To be exact.
there's no reason for me to run away.

9
00:00:24.040 --> 00:00:26.900
Before I am Lee Gilyoung's son.
I am Lee Chaeha.

10
00:00:27.620 --> 00:00:30.620
And now.
I'm Prosecutor Ju Taeseon's investigator.

11
00:00:30.860 --> 00:00:33.170
I will continue to do what I should.

12
00:00:36.950 --> 00:00:39.090
I'll keep belittling you.

13
00:00:39.220 --> 00:00:42.130
As long as you're Lee Gilyoung's son.

14
00:00:45.830 --> 00:00:47.280
Do whatever you want.

15
00:00:48.490 --> 00:00:50.630
You can fire me if you want.

16
00:00:51.060 --> 00:00:53.060
I won't resign first.

17
00:00:53.490 --> 00:00:54.640
I'm curious—

18
00:00:56.060 --> 00:00:57.700
who will give up first?

19
00:00:58.260 --> 00:00:59.000
Also.

20
00:01:00.180 --> 00:01:02.300
that darn respect thing—

21
00:01:02.640 --> 00:01:03.860
don't do it.

22
00:01:04.430 --> 00:01:06.140
Be it you respecting me.

23
00:01:06.310 --> 00:01:08.110
or me being respected by you—

24
00:01:08.230 --> 00:01:10.090
the thought of that makes me sick.

25
00:01:12.380 --> 00:01:13.810
I'll give you one week.

26
00:01:14.830 --> 00:01:16.140
Just one week.

27
00:01:30.340 --> 00:01:32.490
[Park Siwoo]

28
00:01:34.930 --> 00:01:37.420
[Kim Yunsik]

29
00:01:42.729 --> 00:01:44.350
[Kwak Seunghwan]
[Because of inheritance?]

30
00:01:45.110 --> 00:01:46.550
[Koryoin Mr. Kim overdosed on drugs]

31
00:01:46.990 --> 00:01:48.440
[Found in a small room
on the second floor]

32
00:01:48.670 --> 00:01:50.880
[Last abandoned mine in Danhyeon
has been converted into a casino...]

33
00:01:51.430 --> 00:01:53.470
[Led by Ohsong Construction. 'Danhyeon Land' Integrated Resort (Casino. Hotel. Theme Park) to be built—
Officially secures $400M in foreign investment]

34
00:01:53.710 --> 00:01:58.000
[Casino Industry's First Female Executive…
Pledges "Transparent Operations. Regional Co-Prosperity"]

35
00:01:58.110 --> 00:01:59.880
[Danhyeon City "Casino Boss Murdered"...
Suspect Identified as Driver. Mr. Lee]

36
00:02:06.390 --> 00:02:08.750
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

37
00:02:20.810 --> 00:02:26.700
[Late Yoon Soyeon]

38
00:02:50.060 --> 00:02:51.510
[Ohsong Group Casino Hotel
Corruption Case]

39
00:02:50.290 --> 00:02:53.810
The Ohsong Group Casino Hotel's bidding
must have something to do

40
00:02:53.810 --> 00:02:55.440
with Kang Woosung's case.

41
00:02:55.930 --> 00:02:59.350
Kang Woosung
made Ohsong lose the hotel bidding before.

42
00:02:58.090 --> 00:02:58.890
[Crime scene photos]

43
00:03:00.050 --> 00:03:03.440
After Kang Woosung died.
Ohsong Construction won the bid.

44
00:03:04.060 --> 00:03:05.460
You know that too. right?

45
00:03:05.810 --> 00:03:08.740
The murder of the casino's first boss.
Kang Woosung.

46
00:03:08.750 --> 00:03:10.880
The culprit was his friend and driver.

47
00:03:11.360 --> 00:03:13.500
Lee Gilyoung. who killed Kang Woosung.

48
00:03:13.500 --> 00:03:14.560
Lee Gilyoung's son

49
00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:17.190
submitted the diary he wrote that day
as evidence

50
00:03:17.190 --> 00:03:18.230
and testified.

51
00:03:18.620 --> 00:03:20.780
He said the 1 million won
Lee Gilyoung had

52
00:03:20.780 --> 00:03:23.150
wasn't the money
he stole after killing Mr. Kang Woosung.

53
00:03:21.180 --> 00:03:21.740
[Friday. January 21. 2011
Something interesting happened today. Dad went to see Uncle Woosung. and Uncle Woosung gave him a bonus of 1 million won!
Because of that. Dad looked super happy all day long.]

54
00:03:21.740 --> 00:03:22.500
[He even smiled and said. "Your Uncle Woosung gave me this. take it as your pocket money." Seeing Dad like that made me feel really happy too.
Lately. since Dad started working with Uncle Woosung. he's been smiling a whole lot more.]

55
00:03:22.500 --> 00:03:23.060
[It's such a relief that they are friends. I hope that when I grow up.
I can make great friends just like Dad did. Today will probably be a special day that I'll remember for a very long time.]

56
00:03:23.450 --> 00:03:26.579
It says that it was a bonus
his father got from Kang Woosung.

57
00:03:26.579 --> 00:03:27.690
It's just a diary.

58
00:03:28.900 --> 00:03:30.230
You believe him?

59
00:03:30.810 --> 00:03:32.020
Who would believe

60
00:03:32.050 --> 00:03:33.360
the words of a murderer's son?

61
00:03:33.360 --> 00:03:36.470
I know. Both the prosecutor and the police

62
00:03:36.710 --> 00:03:39.860
didn't care about what he said.

63
00:03:40.430 --> 00:03:42.829
But what if he didn't lie?

64
00:03:43.829 --> 00:03:46.340
Why would Lee Gilyoung kill Kang Woosung?

65
00:03:46.430 --> 00:03:47.900
He gets 3 million won a month—

66
00:03:47.900 --> 00:03:49.960
would he do this just to get 1 million?

67
00:03:50.940 --> 00:03:52.440
Something's off.

68
00:03:52.780 --> 00:03:55.340
All the evidence points to Lee Gilyoung.

69
00:03:55.510 --> 00:03:57.560
We are people who solve cases
with evidence.

70
00:03:57.560 --> 00:03:58.770
not by instinct.

71
00:04:03.020 --> 00:04:04.060
I don't know how the higher-ups found out.

72
00:04:04.060 --> 00:04:06.380
They've been trying to press this down.

73
00:04:06.700 --> 00:04:09.640
Feels like it has something to do
with Ohsong Group.

74
00:04:09.900 --> 00:04:13.030
I'm sure they're doing this
because something's amiss.

75
00:04:13.860 --> 00:04:17.290
Prosecutor Ju. please help me.

76
00:04:18.050 --> 00:04:20.250
I need to meet those kids.

77
00:04:20.810 --> 00:04:21.740
Kids?

78
00:04:22.040 --> 00:04:25.330
Yes. Lee Gilyoung's son.

79
00:04:26.950 --> 00:04:29.610
and Kang Woosung's son
who was home that day.

80
00:04:30.220 --> 00:04:31.980
I-I'll help you.

81
00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:35.950
Leave the kids to me.

82
00:04:38.270 --> 00:04:40.080
Thank you. Taeseon.

83
00:04:41.150 --> 00:04:42.800
Thank you so much.

84
00:04:49.409 --> 00:04:51.960
[Suspect: Lee Gilyoung]
[Charge: Robbery and murder]

85
00:04:51.520 --> 00:04:53.810
Lee Gilyoung's son. Lee Chaeha.

86
00:04:55.740 --> 00:04:58.940
A murderer's son
was admitted to the Police University?

87
00:04:55.750 --> 00:04:58.170
[Lee Chaeha. Top Police Graduate:
"A World Where the Innocent Aren't Wronged"]

88
00:05:00.750 --> 00:05:03.710
Does he actually think
his dad is innocent?

89
00:05:03.970 --> 00:05:06.590
I wonder if he's shameless
or just foolish.

90
00:05:10.460 --> 00:05:11.430
[Yoon Soyeon]

91
00:05:20.530 --> 00:05:22.990
The number you have dialed
is not available.

92
00:05:32.409 --> 00:05:34.409
Hello. Prosecutor Yoon. What's up?

93
00:05:34.960 --> 00:05:36.090
Prosecutor Ju...

94
00:05:38.350 --> 00:05:39.820
Soyeon...

95
00:05:45.310 --> 00:05:47.720
[Late Yoon Soyeon]

96
00:06:03.700 --> 00:06:04.900
Director Tak?

97
00:06:07.720 --> 00:06:09.480
Oh. Taeseon.

98
00:06:09.930 --> 00:06:11.150
What brings you here?

99
00:06:11.480 --> 00:06:15.220
Today is Prosecutor Yoon's
death anniversary.

100
00:06:15.870 --> 00:06:17.030
What about you?

101
00:06:17.750 --> 00:06:21.750
Ah. so Soyeon is resting here.

102
00:06:22.080 --> 00:06:26.810
My sister. who passed away when she was young.
is here. so I come here from time to time.

103
00:06:27.180 --> 00:06:30.760
I didn't know you had a sister.

104
00:06:30.860 --> 00:06:32.130
[Late Tak Jisuk]

105
00:06:32.150 --> 00:06:34.010
You two must have been very close.

106
00:06:34.270 --> 00:06:37.930
She passed away when I was a teenager.
so you probably didn't know.

107
00:06:39.880 --> 00:06:41.180
By the way.

108
00:06:41.440 --> 00:06:42.760
you should forget about the past.

109
00:06:42.760 --> 00:06:46.100
Why do you keep coming to visit
and seeking pain?

110
00:06:48.380 --> 00:06:51.090
You seem cold.

111
00:06:51.220 --> 00:06:53.000
but you care about relationships.

112
00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:54.800
I couldn't even help.

113
00:06:55.070 --> 00:06:57.200
So what if I cherish my relationships?

114
00:07:00.570 --> 00:07:03.500
There's a nice
knife-cut noodle restaurant nearby.

115
00:07:03.550 --> 00:07:05.080
Let's eat before we go to work.

116
00:07:05.080 --> 00:07:05.790
Sure.

117
00:07:06.280 --> 00:07:07.050
Let's go.

118
00:07:14.760 --> 00:07:16.050
[Late Tak Jisuk]

119
00:07:35.650 --> 00:07:37.320
Darn it.

120
00:07:38.190 --> 00:07:39.870
Seojun. are you okay?

121
00:07:40.930 --> 00:07:42.320
You've gone way too far.

122
00:07:42.800 --> 00:07:44.380
Ditching us. your seniors.

123
00:07:44.540 --> 00:07:46.350
and going ahead to get a position
in the prosecutor's office.

124
00:07:46.350 --> 00:07:47.930
you've become so arrogant.

125
00:07:48.450 --> 00:07:49.550
I'm sorry.

126
00:08:03.690 --> 00:08:04.650
Sorry.

127
00:08:22.740 --> 00:08:24.770
Because I don't want to run away.

128
00:08:25.980 --> 00:08:27.510
I have no reason to run away.

129
00:08:34.350 --> 00:08:36.950
Before I am Lee Gilyoung's son.
I am Lee Chaeha.

130
00:08:37.580 --> 00:08:39.720
I won't resign first.

131
00:08:44.350 --> 00:08:45.450
Oh. you're here.

132
00:08:51.030 --> 00:08:53.490
He must have pulled
a few all-nighters here.

133
00:08:54.120 --> 00:08:56.520
Mr. Lee is working too hard.

134
00:08:58.740 --> 00:09:01.200
Tell him to come to my office
when he comes in.

135
00:09:01.260 --> 00:09:02.210
Sure.

136
00:09:05.340 --> 00:09:06.810
Goodness.

137
00:09:25.700 --> 00:09:28.340
You read all the files in a week.
I'm impressed.

138
00:09:28.560 --> 00:09:31.360
You also found all kinds of laws
and examples.

139
00:09:31.590 --> 00:09:34.030
Even for cases with results.

140
00:09:34.320 --> 00:09:36.900
you still kept your indictment.
I'll commend you for that.

141
00:09:36.900 --> 00:09:39.090
After all. for example. in the first case.

142
00:09:39.090 --> 00:09:42.120
the charge wasn't attempted murder.
but rape.

143
00:09:42.460 --> 00:09:44.720
The suspect said himself
that he kept strangling the victim

144
00:09:44.720 --> 00:09:46.140
until he thought they were dead.

145
00:09:46.140 --> 00:09:48.100
So I think we should raise the case
as attempted murder.

146
00:09:48.100 --> 00:09:49.640
I think so too.

147
00:09:50.300 --> 00:09:52.830
This prosecutor
just glossed over this case.

148
00:09:55.590 --> 00:09:56.650
But...

149
00:09:58.570 --> 00:10:00.370
what disappointed me is

150
00:10:04.300 --> 00:10:06.280
I didn't see any reason

151
00:10:06.500 --> 00:10:09.630
why I would choose you
over other senior investigators.

152
00:10:11.140 --> 00:10:13.340
As an investigator. you're just so-so.

153
00:10:13.440 --> 00:10:16.170
Just wait for your return
to the fine department.

154
00:10:21.920 --> 00:10:22.960
What are you waiting for?

155
00:10:22.960 --> 00:10:23.830
Get out.

156
00:10:30.390 --> 00:10:33.060
Maybe the murder weapon wasn't an awl.

157
00:10:34.780 --> 00:10:38.380
I'm talking about the murder
of Granny Park at Ohsong Apartment.

158
00:10:38.620 --> 00:10:41.420
The one that happened 7 years ago
in Danhyeon City.

159
00:10:42.550 --> 00:10:44.180
Go on.

160
00:10:44.510 --> 00:10:47.960
The victim was a 70-year-old lady
who lived alone in an apartment.

161
00:10:47.960 --> 00:10:49.310
She was a gynecologist.

162
00:10:49.970 --> 00:10:53.440
The body was already rotting
when it was found.

163
00:10:56.520 --> 00:11:00.580
The killer stabbed the awl
into the middle of her neck.

164
00:11:01.180 --> 00:11:03.140
I looked for the same awl.

165
00:11:03.520 --> 00:11:05.350
The length is 25 cm.

166
00:11:05.610 --> 00:11:07.340
and the thickness is about 3 mm.

167
00:11:07.390 --> 00:11:10.260
But according to the autopsy report.

168
00:11:10.440 --> 00:11:12.120
the diameter was 5 mm.

169
00:11:18.460 --> 00:11:20.420
Why did they change the weapon?

170
00:11:20.560 --> 00:11:22.420
They could've just taken it away.

171
00:11:24.770 --> 00:11:26.620
If the weapon wasn't at the scene.

172
00:11:26.620 --> 00:11:29.850
the police would've tried their best
to find it.

173
00:11:29.940 --> 00:11:33.270
Then why did the killer take the real weapon?
Afraid of getting exposed?

174
00:11:33.270 --> 00:11:36.190
Or is it to use it for their next crime?

175
00:11:36.500 --> 00:11:37.420
Well...

176
00:11:42.080 --> 00:11:43.040
One.

177
00:11:44.390 --> 00:11:45.550
Two.

178
00:11:46.310 --> 00:11:47.630
Three.

179
00:11:48.680 --> 00:11:49.690
Four.

180
00:11:53.640 --> 00:11:54.940
A whole 20 times.

181
00:11:55.250 --> 00:11:56.630
Overkill.

182
00:11:57.070 --> 00:11:58.720
A typical vendetta killing.

183
00:11:59.170 --> 00:12:01.900
What do you think?

184
00:12:10.050 --> 00:12:12.590
Lee Gilyoung also killed someone
with an awl.

185
00:12:31.380 --> 00:12:34.780
But the culprit who turned himself
in was an old man in his 70s.

186
00:12:34.810 --> 00:12:37.160
He had no criminal record
and had nothing to do with the victim.

187
00:12:37.160 --> 00:12:38.630
Why. then?

188
00:12:39.420 --> 00:12:40.720
Why did he kill her?

189
00:12:41.280 --> 00:12:43.160
And why did he turn himself in?

190
00:12:44.810 --> 00:12:46.570
Is it related to other cases?

191
00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:50.710
What about the needle mark
on Koryoin Kim

192
00:12:50.880 --> 00:12:52.450
and his nicotine levels?

193
00:12:55.070 --> 00:12:56.090
Get out.

194
00:12:59.840 --> 00:13:00.760
What?

195
00:13:00.970 --> 00:13:01.900
Get out.

196
00:13:04.490 --> 00:13:05.610
Chaeha!

197
00:13:09.790 --> 00:13:10.960
Lee Chaeha.

198
00:13:11.250 --> 00:13:12.450
Who is it—

199
00:13:19.120 --> 00:13:21.510
Long time no see. Nephew.

200
00:13:23.740 --> 00:13:25.470
You've grown up.

201
00:13:27.020 --> 00:13:28.520
We'll go take a walk.

202
00:13:34.820 --> 00:13:38.660
[Investigator. Lee Chaeha]

203
00:13:37.880 --> 00:13:38.780
Hey.

204
00:13:40.210 --> 00:13:41.980
You're quite successful. huh?

205
00:13:44.640 --> 00:13:45.780
Gosh.

206
00:13:46.930 --> 00:13:48.680
Uncle. let's talk outside.

207
00:13:48.820 --> 00:13:50.860
Goodness.

208
00:13:54.260 --> 00:13:57.570
I heard you work at
the prosecutor's office. You must be busy.

209
00:13:57.570 --> 00:13:58.890
I couldn't reach you.

210
00:14:00.570 --> 00:14:02.440
Do the people here know?

211
00:14:05.590 --> 00:14:07.450
That you're the son of a murderer.

212
00:14:08.760 --> 00:14:10.230
The orphan of a murderer—

213
00:14:10.390 --> 00:14:12.220
I raised you.

214
00:14:12.340 --> 00:14:14.440
You should repay me.

215
00:14:16.410 --> 00:14:18.080
Until the day you die.

216
00:14:19.510 --> 00:14:21.840
Is your laundromat not doing well lately?

217
00:14:21.850 --> 00:14:23.510
You need money from me. right?

218
00:14:23.560 --> 00:14:24.620
I'll give it to you.

219
00:14:24.830 --> 00:14:27.030
I'll give you money. so don't come here—

220
00:14:33.100 --> 00:14:34.030
Darn it.

221
00:14:39.900 --> 00:14:40.940
You know what?

222
00:14:42.370 --> 00:14:45.230
No one would welcome a guy like you.

223
00:14:48.700 --> 00:14:51.130
No one will like you.

224
00:14:52.160 --> 00:14:55.850
I loathe you with every fiber of my being
because you are Lee Chaeha.

225
00:14:55.850 --> 00:14:58.090
So no matter what happens to you.

226
00:14:58.360 --> 00:14:59.860
and no matter what I do.

227
00:15:00.640 --> 00:15:02.100
you should just suck it up.

228
00:15:03.700 --> 00:15:05.240
You should just suck it up.

229
00:15:16.940 --> 00:15:18.610
Who are you?

230
00:15:19.060 --> 00:15:20.260
I'm leaving. Chaeha.

231
00:15:21.910 --> 00:15:23.550
Keep in touch.

232
00:15:28.020 --> 00:15:30.020
-Please take care of Chaeha.
-Okay.

233
00:15:31.250 --> 00:15:32.430
Goodbye!

234
00:15:35.390 --> 00:15:36.370
Mr. Lee.

235
00:15:38.440 --> 00:15:39.440
Is that your dad?

236
00:15:39.650 --> 00:15:40.640
Oh...

237
00:15:43.870 --> 00:15:45.040
-Hello—
-What?

238
00:15:45.390 --> 00:15:47.010
You want us to submit the video evidence?

239
00:15:47.010 --> 00:15:49.740
If we left it out. then so be it!

240
00:15:50.000 --> 00:15:51.920
Are you suspecting us police?

241
00:15:52.400 --> 00:15:56.060
Why? Are you suspecting us of
not asking them to gargle on purpose?

242
00:15:56.210 --> 00:15:58.180
Get that Lee Chaeha on the call.

243
00:15:58.460 --> 00:15:59.370
Mr. Lee.

244
00:15:59.660 --> 00:16:01.030
the police
from the traffic department said

245
00:16:01.030 --> 00:16:03.610
they forgot to ask them to gargle
before they did the breath test.

246
00:16:03.610 --> 00:16:06.700
It's a violation of procedure.
so we can't raise the case.

247
00:16:06.700 --> 00:16:07.960
It's non-indictment.

248
00:16:11.190 --> 00:16:13.850
I need to verify that the procedure
was improper

249
00:16:13.850 --> 00:16:16.050
when Oh Jayeon was doing the breath test

250
00:16:16.050 --> 00:16:17.780
so I can report to the prosecutor that
she is innocent—

251
00:16:17.780 --> 00:16:18.650
Prosecutor?

252
00:16:18.650 --> 00:16:19.740
Which prosecutor's office are you from?

253
00:16:19.740 --> 00:16:21.520
Are you a prosecutor? Huh?

254
00:16:23.830 --> 00:16:24.940
Detective Ma.

255
00:16:25.080 --> 00:16:26.930
Did my staff ask for too much?

256
00:16:28.440 --> 00:16:29.770
Prosecutor Ju Taeseon.

257
00:16:29.880 --> 00:16:31.050
It's not like that.

258
00:16:31.380 --> 00:16:34.350
I already said that we made a mistake
in the procedure.

259
00:16:34.350 --> 00:16:36.010
Asking us to provide the video

260
00:16:36.060 --> 00:16:37.360
seems a bit too much.

261
00:16:37.420 --> 00:16:39.370
You're forwarding the case
with a recommendation for non-indictment

262
00:16:39.370 --> 00:16:41.880
having drafted nothing but paperwork
without a single shred of evidence.

263
00:16:41.880 --> 00:16:44.290
and now instead of apologizing
to my staff. you're shouting at them?

264
00:16:44.290 --> 00:16:45.590
Are you trying to handle
a judicial process

265
00:16:45.590 --> 00:16:48.430
by ignoring procedures
and just building personal connections?

266
00:16:48.430 --> 00:16:50.220
Prosecutor Ju. that's not what I mean.

267
00:16:50.220 --> 00:16:52.820
With you responding to our request
in this way.

268
00:16:52.990 --> 00:16:55.560
we can only be suspicious of you.

269
00:16:55.790 --> 00:16:57.860
Where was the breath test done?

270
00:16:58.300 --> 00:16:59.560
At the police station.

271
00:17:00.080 --> 00:17:01.340
Senior Assistant Lee.

272
00:17:01.550 --> 00:17:03.450
do the police have any records of them

273
00:17:03.450 --> 00:17:05.630
redoing the breath test
or doing a blood test?

274
00:17:05.630 --> 00:17:07.140
There wasn't another breath test.

275
00:17:07.140 --> 00:17:09.099
but they did a blood test 2 days later.

276
00:17:09.099 --> 00:17:11.829
But 2 days later.
the alcohol content was zero...

277
00:17:13.710 --> 00:17:15.390
When you realized the violation
of the procedure.

278
00:17:15.390 --> 00:17:18.790
you should've done the breath test again
or done a blood test.

279
00:17:18.839 --> 00:17:20.980
Do you think another test 2 days after
make any sense?

280
00:17:20.980 --> 00:17:22.609
The reports Senior Assistant Lee
is writing

281
00:17:22.609 --> 00:17:24.420
will be submitted in my name.

282
00:17:24.660 --> 00:17:26.750
Apologize to my assistant immediately.

283
00:17:26.750 --> 00:17:29.150
and send me the related evidence
right now.

284
00:17:29.500 --> 00:17:30.230
Prosecutor.

285
00:17:30.270 --> 00:17:31.160
Prosecutor!

286
00:17:36.110 --> 00:17:39.100
[Prosecution Office]

287
00:17:37.730 --> 00:17:39.850
I got Oh Jayeon's CCTV footage.

288
00:17:57.830 --> 00:17:58.900
It was drugs.

289
00:17:59.180 --> 00:18:00.780
What? Drugs?

290
00:18:00.880 --> 00:18:03.110
Go to the police station right now.
get the blood sample.

291
00:18:03.110 --> 00:18:04.320
and hand it over to the Forensic Center.

292
00:18:04.320 --> 00:18:05.660
I'll let them know ahead of time.

293
00:18:05.660 --> 00:18:06.610
Got it.

294
00:18:07.130 --> 00:18:09.130
Do you think the police didn't know?

295
00:18:09.430 --> 00:18:11.180
The police at Danhyeon Police Station

296
00:18:11.180 --> 00:18:13.040
are different from other places.

297
00:18:13.240 --> 00:18:16.900
Many of them are taking bribes
from the casino and Ohsong Construction.

298
00:18:16.900 --> 00:18:20.630
Should we reinvestigate whether
Oh Jayeon was abusing drugs then?

299
00:18:21.070 --> 00:18:22.150
No.

300
00:18:23.540 --> 00:18:25.940
We will close the case without indictment.

301
00:18:26.090 --> 00:18:28.980
They won't be charged due to
the improper procedure done by the police.

302
00:18:28.980 --> 00:18:30.250
Then why...

303
00:18:32.600 --> 00:18:33.610
Mr. Song.

304
00:18:33.870 --> 00:18:36.070
Please go and get
the blood samples quickly.

305
00:18:36.070 --> 00:18:38.790
We shouldn't pass it over to
the Forensic Center through official procedures.

306
00:18:38.790 --> 00:18:40.350
You have to be as careful as possible.

307
00:18:40.350 --> 00:18:41.200
Understood.

308
00:18:50.360 --> 00:18:52.950
If there are traces of drugs
in the blood sample.

309
00:18:52.950 --> 00:18:54.150
we should bring in Oh Jayeon...

310
00:18:54.150 --> 00:18:55.480
Are you the prosecutor?

311
00:18:55.560 --> 00:18:57.250
Stop talking back and do as I say.

312
00:18:57.250 --> 00:18:58.170
But...

313
00:18:58.370 --> 00:19:00.220
If Oh Jayeon's drug was meth.

314
00:19:00.380 --> 00:19:03.430
it could be the same drug the Koryoin
was smuggling.

315
00:19:03.550 --> 00:19:06.240
What if she's related to the Koryoin case?

316
00:19:06.390 --> 00:19:09.140
I forgot this for a moment
and was just going to let it slide.

317
00:19:09.140 --> 00:19:13.650
but Senior Assistant Lee. didn't we agree
you'd resign and go back to the fine department?

318
00:19:13.650 --> 00:19:14.730
Prosecutor Ju.

319
00:19:15.320 --> 00:19:17.780
Why? Going to ask me for another chance?

320
00:19:18.660 --> 00:19:19.600
Yes.

321
00:19:22.430 --> 00:19:23.430
Sure.

322
00:19:24.480 --> 00:19:27.540
I plan to give you an old case.

323
00:19:27.710 --> 00:19:28.860
Anything's fine.

324
00:19:28.970 --> 00:19:31.640
-Just leave it to me—
-This case is closed.

325
00:19:31.800 --> 00:19:34.860
The suspect committed suicide

326
00:19:34.990 --> 00:19:36.790
before the trial result was out.

327
00:19:38.120 --> 00:19:38.960
Hey!

328
00:19:39.710 --> 00:19:40.930
Hurry!

329
00:19:41.190 --> 00:19:42.240
Stop No. 6430!

330
00:19:42.400 --> 00:19:43.910
Wake up. No. 6430!

331
00:19:46.130 --> 00:19:48.540
Like most murders.

332
00:19:48.670 --> 00:19:51.270
all the evidence points
to the suspect. but...

333
00:19:52.840 --> 00:19:55.660
some people just refuse to admit it—

334
00:19:59.240 --> 00:20:01.090
the murderer himself.

335
00:20:02.120 --> 00:20:04.900
and the son of the murderer.

336
00:20:07.020 --> 00:20:08.330
You know that too. right?

337
00:20:08.330 --> 00:20:11.030
I hate bastards who refuse to admit

338
00:20:11.200 --> 00:20:12.870
to the core.

339
00:20:15.810 --> 00:20:17.720
But I was curious.

340
00:20:22.180 --> 00:20:23.250
Did that kid

341
00:20:26.450 --> 00:20:29.910
really think
his father didn't kill anyone?

342
00:20:34.820 --> 00:20:37.940
The assailant in the casino owner
Kang Woosung's awl murder case

343
00:20:37.940 --> 00:20:40.990
was Kang Woosung

344
00:20:41.240 --> 00:20:43.440
and Oh Jayeon's high school classmate.

345
00:20:45.800 --> 00:20:47.670
[Lee Gilyoung]

346
00:20:56.840 --> 00:20:58.500
I wanted to be acknowledged.

347
00:20:59.440 --> 00:21:02.500
I wanted to be acknowledged
by the upright prosecutor.

348
00:21:03.240 --> 00:21:04.570
Ju Taeseon.

349
00:21:06.460 --> 00:21:08.200
Um. Prosecutor Ju Taeseon.

350
00:21:08.600 --> 00:21:10.990
I'm happy to have worked with you today.

351
00:21:11.210 --> 00:21:14.060
Ever since I saw an article about you
when I was in university.

352
00:21:14.060 --> 00:21:15.190
I've respected you.

353
00:21:16.530 --> 00:21:17.950
One day.

354
00:21:18.770 --> 00:21:21.710
I'll be able to tell you

355
00:21:21.860 --> 00:21:24.350
that I'm different from the murderer.
Lee Gilyoung.

356
00:21:24.350 --> 00:21:26.050
But all this

357
00:21:27.280 --> 00:21:28.690
was a trap set by him.

358
00:21:28.910 --> 00:21:31.170
You will re-investigate it personally—

359
00:21:31.530 --> 00:21:33.460
the case of Kang Woosung's murder.

360
00:21:33.660 --> 00:21:35.970
and the murderer. Lee Gilyoung.

361
00:21:46.290 --> 00:21:48.450
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

362
00:21:48.430 --> 00:21:49.610
How should I put this? Putting this on

363
00:21:48.490 --> 00:21:51.680
[Next Episode]

364
00:21:49.790 --> 00:21:52.840
makes me feel that
I'll be as capable as you in the future.

365
00:21:52.840 --> 00:21:53.620
Hubby!

366
00:21:54.410 --> 00:21:55.160
Please.

367
00:21:55.360 --> 00:21:56.240
Please.

368
00:21:56.420 --> 00:21:57.240
Police!

369
00:21:57.390 --> 00:21:59.570
You have other suspects in mind. right?

370
00:21:59.570 --> 00:22:00.410
Mr. Lee.

371
00:22:00.490 --> 00:22:01.760
you're heading straight back
to the accommodation. right?

372
00:22:01.760 --> 00:22:02.350
Yes.

373
00:22:02.370 --> 00:22:04.100
No. he'll come with me.

374
00:22:07.630 --> 00:22:09.710
It'll be more suspicious if you dodge.

375
00:22:09.710 --> 00:22:11.930
You avoid me every time we touch.

376
00:22:12.130 --> 00:22:13.950
That makes people more suspicious.

377
00:22:13.950 --> 00:22:14.830
Lee Chaeha.

378
00:22:15.250 --> 00:22:16.820
You started this.
